replies.body:
I'm pretty ok(ish) at support when autofilled and usually go {{champion:61}} 

My thoughts on the role are well..yea, it's an important role. While "ADCs have a bad early game!" is such a huge lie {{champion:29}} {{champion:119}} {{champion:236}} {{champion:51}} {{champion:133}} (heck, even {{champion:67}} {{champion:96}} can outtrade mages, assassins, and tanks/bruisers/juggernaut/whateverfancywordyouuse.) you're still there peeling  for people. Unless you're gold or whatever, a lot of supports are just gonna be potatoes standing behind an adc doing pretty much nothing unless they're playing Blitzcrank or Thresh, but  as you go higher up you see them actually picking people out, ccing assassins, etc. I play ADC a pretty good amount, and even then I've only had a handful of supports that actually TRADE with the enemy laners as a ranged support, and try to skirmish/all in as a tanky support.

If you're good at the role you carry if your adc knows how to right click. If they don't, then go support your midlaner when the laning phase ends.
